  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Brush the bottom and sides of a 9x13 inch baking dish with olive oil.",
    "Arrange the red and yellow bell peppers in the baking dish.",
    "In a bowl, mix the shredded cheese, crumbled Cotija cheese, salt, black pepper, chili powder, and garlic.",
    "Pour the cheese mixture over the bell peppers.",
    "Drizzle the remaining olive oil over the top.",
    "Sprinkle the chopped cilantro over the top.",
    "Cover the baking dish with aluminum foil and bake for 20 minutes.",
    "Remove the foil and continue baking for an additional 10-12 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly."
